# =============================================================================
# session-blacklist — Default blacklisted startup commands
# =============================================================================
# Commands listed here are stubbed out as no-ops during the rc sourcing phase
# of a recorded homelab session. This suppresses startup noise that would
# otherwise pollute the transcript with unparseable output.
#
# Stubs are unset immediately after rc sourcing completes, so all commands
# listed here remain fully available during the session itself.
#
# To add your own entries, create:
#   ~/.config/homelab/session-blacklist
# One command name per line. Lines starting with # are ignored.
# =============================================================================

# --- System info / fetch tools ---
neofetch
fastfetch
pfetch
screenfetch
